WEBVTT

00:10.492 --> 00:12.132
It's the closing minutes
of the World Cup.

00:12.195 --> 00:14.267
Brad Taylor steals the ball
and dribbles to the right,

00:14.297 --> 00:17.265
cuts back to the left, shoots!
It's a goal!

00:17.333 --> 00:21.336
Goal, goal, goal!

00:21.404 --> 00:23.138
Goal!

00:23.706 --> 00:25.206
Oh, yeah!

00:27.409 --> 00:29.678
So you're studying
hard today, huh?

00:29.745 --> 00:33.448
Yeah. I'm practicing
for the SAT test.

00:33.515 --> 00:36.251
Is this the part where
they ask you to make rain?

00:37.887 --> 00:40.055
No, I was just
taking the math test.

00:40.123 --> 00:43.758
Gosh, it was so hard I'm
scared to find out my score.

00:43.827 --> 00:45.627
Well, let's add it up.
How do we do this?

00:45.695 --> 00:47.566
Well, I already did the
adding and the subtracting.

00:47.596 --> 00:49.898
You have to take this number
here and divide it by four.

00:49.966 --> 00:51.366
Well, don't worry.

00:51.434 --> 00:53.936
Math is just simple logic.

00:54.003 --> 00:56.205
Let's see, two, two...

00:56.272 --> 01:01.075
Well, Dad, when you divide,
shouldn't the number get smaller?

01:01.143 --> 01:03.812
I've been dividing since I was a kid.
That is your score.

01:03.879 --> 01:06.581
Forty-two hundred, baby!

01:06.649 --> 01:09.351
Dad, the highest
possible score is 800.

01:09.419 --> 01:11.653
You know what?
I bet you added a zero to the 420.

01:11.720 --> 01:14.489
Don't be silly.
You add a zero to 420, you still get 420.

01:16.258 --> 01:17.792
- Yeah, you're right.
- Hi, guys.

01:17.827 --> 01:18.860
Hi.

01:18.928 --> 01:21.163
So what do you think?

01:22.064 --> 01:23.398
New hair?

01:23.465 --> 01:24.866
No!

01:24.934 --> 01:26.067
New pants?

01:26.135 --> 01:29.404
No! New couch!
New couch!

01:29.839 --> 01:32.708
What new couch?

01:32.775 --> 01:35.277
I cannot believe
that you didn't notice it.

01:35.344 --> 01:37.512
It's been here since
early this morning.

01:37.580 --> 01:42.049
I spent six weeks picking this thing out.
I love it. Love it.

01:42.117 --> 01:47.656
I'm gonna lie down here
and never get up. Ever. Never.

01:47.723 --> 01:49.891
Well, Mom, I got a
420 on my math test.

01:49.958 --> 01:53.795
What? Oh, my God!

01:53.863 --> 01:56.598
You're never gonna get into
UCLA with scores like that,

01:56.666 --> 01:58.400
no matter how
well you play soccer.

01:58.468 --> 02:01.770
I know, but I hate math. I'd rather
hit myself in the head with a hammer.

02:01.838 --> 02:04.038
Don't be too sure.
It really hurts.

